54.3	Cryptosporidium	Cryptosporidium	Cryptosporidium is a protozoan that can cause gastro-intestinal illness with diarrhea in humans. Cryptosporidium is the organism most commonly isolated in HIV positive patients presenting with diarrhea. Treatment is symptomatic, with fluid rehydration, electrolyte correction and management of any pain.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Cryptosporidium_muris.jpg/270px-Cryptosporidium_muris.jpg
